<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2874] Highlighting overlapping tokens outputs doubled words</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2874</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;If for the text &quot;the fox did not jump&quot; we generate following tokens :&lt;br/&gt;
(the, 0, 0-3),(&lt;/p&gt;
{fox}
&lt;p&gt;,0,0-7),(fox,1,4-7),(did,2,8-11),(not,3,12,15),(jump,4,16,18)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If TermVector for field is stored WITH_OFFSETS and not WITH_POSITIONS_OFFSETS, highlighing would output&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;the&amp;lt;em&amp;gt;the fox&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt; did not jump&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I join a patch with 2 additive JUnit tests and a fix of TokenSources class where token ordering by offset did&apos;nt manage well overlapping tokens.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
